The paper deals with compressed sensing reconstruction problem and analyzes it through the state evolution method using an approximate message passing (AMP) algorithm. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Machine Learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of random, band-diagonal sensing matrices, which could potentially fall under the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on the empirical distribution of the signal suggests that it could also belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
